<K2 id="文章结构" load="generation">
文章架构 | Article Scaffold

段落1: 问题陷阱 | Problem Hook [80-100w]
  scene: specific operational context (food processing | stamping | canning | textile)
  failure: the thing that goes wrong when equipment is wrong or misapplied
  ∅vague_openers | ∅"magnets are important" → open on the specific failure

段落2: 机制解释 | Mechanism [150-200w]
  explain: the physics∨engineering behind the Bunting solution
  depth: one level below what a spec sheet shows | ∅textbook | ∅oversimplified
  anchor: named Bunting product∨design∨patent

段落3: 竞争对比 | Contrast [100-120w]
  frame: competitor approach∨industry default → what breaks and why
  ∅competitor_names | reference "standard designs" ∨ "common practice"
  specifics: what failure looks like in production (downtime | contamination | OSHA | recall)

段落4: 选型指南 | Selection Guidance [100-150w]
  rules: when this solution applies | key variables that govern the choice
  examples: 2-3 concrete scenarios with different outcomes
  numbers_preferred: angles | speeds | dimensions | compliance codes | load ratings

段落5: 实施提示 | Field Tips [80-100w]
  practitioner_level: the detail a maintenance tech or process engineer actually needs
  ∅obvious | surface the non-obvious setup parameter∨gotcha
  close: tie back to the operational consequence avoided

声音规则 | Voice Rules
  ∅"Bunting is the best" ∅"industry-leading" ∅"world-class"
  ✓"Bunting's No-Spill Slide Gate" ✓"U.S. Patent No. 6,481,706" ✓"300-series stainless"
  active voice | practitioner "you" | facts carry the authority | ∅adjective stacking
</K2>

